groups.text: You may write me down in history
groups.name: line_000_1

groups.text: You may trod me in the very dirt
groups.name: line_002_6

groups.text: But still, like dust, I'll rise
groups.name: line_003_8

groups.text: Why are you beset with gloom
groups.name: line_005_15

groups.text: Just ‘cause I walk as if I have oil wells
groups.name: line_006_17

groups.text: Just like suns and like moons
groups.name: line_008_23

groups.text: Did you want to see me broken
groups.name: line_012_33

groups.text: Just ‘cause I laugh as if I have gold mines
groups.name: line_018_49

groups.text: You can shoot me with your words
groups.name: line_020_58

groups.text: You can cut me with your lies
groups.name: line_021_61

groups.text: You can kill me with your hatefulness
groups.name: line_022_63

groups.text: But just like life, I'll rise
groups.name: line_023_65

groups.text: Does it come as a surprise
groups.name: line_025_73

groups.text: That I dance as if I have diamonds
groups.name: line_026_75

groups.text: At the meeting of my thighs
groups.name: line_027_82

groups.text: Out of the huts of history's shame
groups.name: line_028_85

groups.text: Up from a past rooted in pain
groups.name: line_030_88

groups.text: A black ocean, leaping and wide
groups.name: line_032_91

groups.text: Welling and swelling I bear in the tide
groups.name: line_033_95

groups.text: Leaving behind nights of terror and fear
groups.name: line_034_100

groups.text: Bringing the gifts that my ancestors gave
groups.name: line_038_110

groups.text: I am the hope and the dream of the slave
groups.name: line_039_114
